{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d0a878c-5274-4c78-a5a1-24420b344d4d","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you a general guide. Here are the key changes to switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Configure your NuGet.org package\n\nOn **nuget.org**, go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers** and add a GitHub Actions trusted publisher with your repo details (owner, repo, workflow file, optional environment).\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Add permissions** to the job:\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n```\n\n**Replace** the `dotnet nuget push` step:\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE (API key):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n\n# AFTER (trusted publishing):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: \"\"          # not needed anymore\n```\n\nActually, the simplest approach uses the **`dotnet` CLI built-in OIDC support** (available in .NET SDK 9+):\n\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key az\n  env:\n    ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_URL: ${{ env.ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_URL }}\n    ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_TOKEN: ${{ env.ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_TOKEN }}\n```\n\n### 3. Remove the secret\n\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**.\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Area | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Authentication | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC (`id-token: write`) |\n| NuGet.org config | API key scoped to package | Trusted publisher entry |\n| Workflow secret | Required | Not needed |\n\nWould you like me to help update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c7edfe79-6fc9-459b-9c81-a68e5700f09c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. I'll provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":595,"requestId":"1FC3:20D256:1804267:1B2BE99:69FE861F"},"id":"09d5fd9b-c3ce-43df-80f5-3b2222f21ca6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:56:13.079Z","parentId":"d20f8561-f28f-4620-a327-3727674183c8"}
